</div><div class='sfContentBlock'><h2>Minors</h2>
Minors can increase students' options when exploring employment, professional, and/or graduate school opportunities. A minor is not required for graduation from LAS, although many students decide to complete a minor to enhance their undergraduate education. Many students choose a minor in an area that particularly piques their interest or relates to their major field. &nbsp;<br />
<br />
A minor may be declared either in the department offering the minor or in the LAS Academic Advising Center. To discuss course selection and progress with minor requirements, <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/students/current-undergraduate/student-affairs/departmental-advising">departmental advisors</a></span> are available.<br />
<br />
The following are the available LAS minors. Select the corresponding link to be directed to the specific requirements for each minor in the&nbsp;<a href="http://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/#e">UIC Undergraduate Catalog</a>:<br />
<h3>LAS Minors</h3>
<a href="http://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/aast/minor/">African American Studies</a><br />
<a href="http://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/anth/minor-anth/">Anthropology</a><br />
<a href="https://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/cl/minor-arab/">Arabic</a><br />
<a href="http://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/bios/minor/">Biological Sciences</a><br />
<a href="http://catalog.uic.edu/ucat/colleges-depts/liberal-arts-sciences/chem/minor-chem/">Chemistry</a><br />
